
Requirements
----------------------------
python>=2.4 (tested on 2.6 )
gnupg
python-gnupg    http://code.google.com/p/python-gnupg/
pygtk
gnome-python



Install
----------------------------
1
---
Copy 'src/secure-nautilus-autorun.py' to a convenient path, rename without .py 
and made id executable

cp src/secure-nautilus-autorun.py ~/bin/secure-nautilus-autorun
chmod +x ~/bin/secure-nautilus-autorun


2
---
Copy secure-nautilus-autorun.desktop to '~/.local/share/applications'.
Edit '~/.local/share/applications/secure-nautilus-autorun.desktop' and replace
path to your 'secure-nautilus-autorun'

3
---
Edit '~/.local/share/applications/mimeapps.list' and replace all
nautilus-autorun-software.desktop
with
secure-nautilus-autorun.desktop

4
---
Restart your session (logout-login)